# String Formatting 
  String formatting is used to insert values into a string using format specifiers like `%s`, `%d`, et

 ✅ Example
String name = "Azmuddin";
int age = 23;
String result = String.format("My name is %s and I am %d years old", name, age);
System.out.println(result);  //My name is Azmuddin and I am 23 years old

## 🔹 Common Format Specifiers

| Specifier | Meaning      |
| --------- | ------------ |
| `%s`      | String       |
| `%d`      | Integer      |
| `%f`      | Float/Double |
| `%c`      | Character    |
| `%b`      | Boolean      |

double price = 99.45678;
System.out.println(String.format("Price: %.2f", price));  //99.46

